By Ibrahim Bello Birnin Kebbi – The Kebbi Government had expended more than N3.62 billion on ongoing township road projects in the state.The Commissioner for Lands and Housing, Alhaji Abubakar Ladan, made this known to newsmen in Birnin Kebbi on Thursday. Ladan said that the money was spent from 2015 till date. He said the amount represented payment of compensation for houses,
property, farmlands and economic trees, affected by development
programmes of the state government. “The payment were made in 15 local government areas of Aliero,
Argungu, Augie, Bagudo, Birnin-Kebbi, Danko/Wasagu, Jega, Kalgo,
Koko/Besse, Maiyama, Sakaba, Shanga, Suru, Yauri and Zuru,” he said. According to him, Gov. Atiku Bagudu, has fulfilled his promise of improving infrastructure and roads in the state. “Some of the road projects are still ongoing and will be completed
within the contractual period, as agreed with contractors,’’ he said. The commissioner said that street lights were provided to beautify and enhance security in the urban centres. “Anybody who comes to our major towns will attest to the street lights on our roads and we will continue to do more,” he said. Ladan noted that the government would ensure the evacuation of
drainage and requested the general public and local governments to
maintain proper clearing of such water channels ahead of the rainy
season, to avoid flooding.